item.dc:creator: @BobDole81 BobDole81
item.description:
@BobDole81 wrote:

Heh, give people more than 30 minutes to respond…

y - 19√y = -60

y - 19√y + 60 = 0

This isn’t really proper factoring, but it’s technically legal…you can check by foiling:

(√y - 15)(√y - 4) = 0

√y - 15 = 0
√y = 15
y = 225

AND

√y - 4 = 0
√y = 4
y = 16

So y = {16, 225}
